The paper deals with blind deconvolution, which is a problem in signal processing. The use of modulated inputs is a technique commonly used in information theory and signal processing to improve the performance of communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses gradient descent algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also deals with subspace recovery, which is a topic in matrix completion and compressed sensing, making cs.MM (Mathematical Methods) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the recovery of unknowns from measurements, which is a topic in optimization and inverse problems, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible category.
